1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:05,360
<i>Why give it to me?</i>

2
00:02:05,440 --> 00:02:09,320
Use the power of the Lek Lai
to help the helpless.

3
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:10,800
<i>We still haven't solved all of it.</i>

4
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:14,360
<i>Blur!</i>

5
00:02:17,360 --> 00:02:18,960
Please don't die, Blur.

6
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:23,240
It feels like
something's moving inside me.

7
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:25,440
It must be the power
of the Klaikot Lek Lai.

8
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:28,680
I brought the head of Bandit Pud,
the one who killed Khun Yod Pakdee.

9
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:33,000
His Excellency and I
will clear your names.

10
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:35,520
<i>I've searched for her in every direction,</i>

11
00:02:36,320 --> 00:02:37,800
yet found no trace.

12
00:02:37,880 --> 00:02:40,160
Take me to meet your family.

13
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:43,600
My father, mother, and little sister

14
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:46,080
were all murdered.

15
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:52,840
Eat.

16
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:00,680
I won't.

17
00:03:05,760 --> 00:03:06,800
If you don't eat it,

18
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:10,120
I'll kill you.

19
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:47,120
I ate it. Will you let me go now?

20
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:50,800
Pud is already in hell.

21
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:53,480
But I want you working for me.

22
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:00,080
And why should I listen to you?

23
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,160
Because it's my order.

24
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:03,680
You obey.

25
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:14,200
And if I don't?

26
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:19,320
<i>Upasakko</i>

27
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,640
<i>pacchuttharami</i>

28
00:04:24,920 --> 00:04:26,400
<i>apacchukhad…</i>

29
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:36,440
The buffalo leeches inside you are hungry.

30
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:40,720
They'll eat your liver and your guts,

31
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:42,000
bit by bit,

32
00:04:43,560 --> 00:04:46,680
until there's nothing left.

33
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,880
I give up.

34
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:03,760
That's all.

35
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:07,200
Pae.

36
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:11,640
Remember, from now on,

37
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:14,360
I am

38
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:16,200
your master.

39
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:28,800
I dream of it every night.

40
00:05:32,280 --> 00:05:33,920
That's the only reason

41
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:36,880
I still want to breathe.

42
00:05:39,880 --> 00:05:42,480
If you catch that bandit,

43
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:44,640
you'll hand him over to the police, right?

44
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:49,280
If I hand them over,

45
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:52,760
they'll just be released
to commit more crimes.

46
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:55,480
Then what will you do?

47
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:58,280
Play judge and executioner?

48
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:03,680
If there's no justice in this world,

49
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:07,000
then I'll use my way.

50
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:12,240
An eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth.

51
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,000
But…

52
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:22,720
killing is a sin.

53
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:26,520
Then what about when
they killed my parents?

54
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:28,520
When they killed my sister?

55
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,960
What has karma ever done to them?

56
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,400
I understand.

57
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:41,120
If it were me, I'd want revenge too.

58
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:52,520
Once I've sent them to hell…

59
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,920
I'll marry you, Orror.

60
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:19,200
Bandit Wad and his son Lasor

61
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:21,520
were not the ones
who slaughtered the family of

62
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:23,160
- Khun Yod Pakdee,
- What are they looking at?

63
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:26,600
- Village Chief of Khuan Phra-ngam.
- Let's go see.

64
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,640
It was Bandit Pud and his gang

65
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:31,440
who committed those heinous crimes.

66
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:35,560
Both Bandit Wad and Lasor have been
completely cleared of all charges.

67
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:38,040
Really?

68
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:40,520
So it was all for nothing?

69
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:42,280
Hey.

70
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:44,480
Oh.

71
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:47,600
Bastards!

72
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,840
- Hey.
- What?

73
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:54,760
What are you doing?
Have you lost your mind?

74
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,600
Disgusting.

75
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:00,160
Is the governor blind and deaf?

76
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:02,920
How could he not know
how vile Bandit Wad truly is?

77
00:08:05,960 --> 00:08:08,760
Not all bandits are evil.

78
00:08:09,280 --> 00:08:12,200
At least Bandit Wad never
slaughtered Khun Yod Pakdee's family.

79
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:14,120
He did it.

80
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:19,160
He killed them in cold blood,
he's worse than a demon.

81
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:21,240
Don't go making reckless accusations.

82
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:24,680
How do you know Bandit Wad did it?

83
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:27,680
Because I am Khun Yod's son,

84
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:29,200
Village Chief of Khuan Phra-ngam.

85
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,640
What did you just say, Blur?

86
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:40,880
The ones who killed my father,

87
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:43,360
my mother, and my sister

88
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:46,040
were Bandit Wad and his son.

89
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,440
I saw it with my own eyes.

90
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:51,880
Yiwha.

91
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:04,920
Did you see the governor's notice?

92
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:07,960
Father Wad, Lasor, and you
are all innocent.

93
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:26,880
I'm sorry.

94
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,080
You deserve a beating for that.

95
00:09:31,720 --> 00:09:33,040
You were reckless,

96
00:09:33,680 --> 00:09:35,000
running off without thinking.

97
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,880
Do you have any idea how worried we were?

98
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:40,240
Come on. Don't scold her.

99
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:44,120
The spirits protected her.

100
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:46,640
She's back safely.
That's all that matters.

101
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:56,200
Your wig, Uncle Chaem.

102
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:58,360
I won't be needing that anymore.

103
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:02,280
Yiwha, aren't you afraid
Saeng might come after you?

104
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:04,880
Her brother

105
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:07,160
is now the governor's assistant.

106
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:10,120
Bigger than Tim ever was.
They wouldn't dare touch her.

107
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:16,360
Lasor is the governor's assistant?

108
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:22,160
Uncle Niem,

109
00:10:22,720 --> 00:10:24,600
I want to see him.

110
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,920
I'm back, Dad.

111
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:48,360
I'm back to reclaim
the vengeance done to our family.

112
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:52,240
Bandit Wad and his son

113
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,800
will pay for what they did.

114
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:58,000
Yiwha!

115
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:02,840
Did you see the governor's notice?

116
00:11:03,440 --> 00:11:06,000
Father Wad, Lasor, and you are innocent.

117
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:07,440
Did you?

118
00:11:09,760 --> 00:11:11,920
Why do you have to be his daughter?

119
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:15,840
Why?!

120
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:53,920
Our informants say

121
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:56,720
Bandit Wad has been spotted
lurking near the residence.

122
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:59,680
Keep a close watch.
He must be captured alive.

123
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:03,480
There's a proclamation
clearing Bandit Wad's name.

124
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:06,600
On what charges
do you intend to arrest him?

125
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:09,520
There is still the old case,

126
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:14,360
conspiring with Bandit Yai
to raid Tycoon Thongyoo's residence.

127
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:16,880
Was there an eyewitness

128
00:12:17,480 --> 00:12:18,760
who saw him commit the crime?

129
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:25,400
Tycoon Thongyoo and his servants
gave firm testimony

130
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:27,840
that it was him.

131
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:32,000
It's possible bandits impersonated him

132
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:36,160
or perhaps the Tycoon
misidentified the culprit.

133
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:40,720
Regardless, Bandit Wad
must be brought in for questioning.

134
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:46,200
I'll handle this case myself.

135
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:51,760
That won't be possible.

136
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:56,480
And why not?

137
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,520
This case falls under police jurisdiction.

138
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:03,000
Besides,

139
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:07,080
Bandit Wad

140
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:10,440
is your biological father,
is he not, Sir Lasor?

141
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:15,280
Don't think

142
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:18,040
being a policeman makes you untouchable.

143
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:20,320
Lasor!

144
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:26,480
Yiwha.

145
00:13:28,520 --> 00:13:29,760
Pun.

146
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,720
What happened, Lasor?

147
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,280
You know him?

148
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:47,600
Uncle Niem.

149
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:51,720
My respects.

150
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:54,880
Keep it for the Buddha.

151
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:04,800
We haven't seen each other for a year.

152
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:07,800
Where did you go? What did you do?

153
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:11,240
Why have you changed so much?

154
00:14:16,760 --> 00:14:18,000
It's a long story.

155
00:14:18,680 --> 00:14:19,840
I'll tell you another time.

156
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:23,160
You disappeared for an entire year.

157
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:25,200
No word whether you were alive or dead.

158
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:29,240
And now you're Sir Lasor,
Governor's Assistant.

159
00:14:31,760 --> 00:14:32,880
As you can see.

160
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:35,600
You and Yiwha

161
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:37,360
could move in with me here.

162
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:40,720
I'll take care of everything.

163
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:42,320
Servants. Comfort.

164
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:44,720
No more hardship like before.

165
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:48,080
I prefer a quiet life.

166
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:51,480
Back in Chum Suea, I wasn't struggling.

167
00:14:51,560 --> 00:14:52,960
I was at peace.

168
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:57,240
Still, seeing how far you've risen,
I'm glad for you.

169
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:00,560
I want Dad to see

170
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:03,160
how far I've come.

171
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:05,040
So he'll finally be proud

172
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:06,880
to have me as his son.

173
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:13,280
Becoming a servant
to those who destroyed Chum Suea,

174
00:15:15,760 --> 00:15:17,680
your father will surely be proud.

175
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:35,440
Then… what about Nui?

176
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:37,600
Where is he now?

177
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:45,560
Last year,

178
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:48,240
he died of jungle fever.

179
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:13,160
How did you suddenly
become the governor's assistant?

180
00:16:16,680 --> 00:16:17,960
I defeated Bandit Pud.

181
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:22,760
He murdered Khun Yod Pakdee's family
and framed Dad and me.

182
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:28,280
So I sent him to hell,

183
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:32,680
cleared our names,
and reclaimed justice for Dad.

184
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:37,760
So Khun Yod's family
was really killed by Bandit Pud,

185
00:16:38,280 --> 00:16:40,400
not by you or Dad.

186
00:16:45,560 --> 00:16:47,200
I told you to stab him!

187
00:16:56,280 --> 00:16:58,400
<i>You won't escape what you've done.</i>

188
00:16:58,480 --> 00:17:02,320
<i>I curse you to live in suffering,</i>

189
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:06,160
<i>to watch those you love</i>
<i>die before your very eyes.</i>

190
00:17:09,960 --> 00:17:11,359
Lasor.

191
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:18,200
Are you alright?

192
00:17:23,040 --> 00:17:25,200
I just haven't fully mastered
the sorcery within me yet.

193
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:28,520
Sorcery?

194
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:31,880
Where did you learn it? Who taught you?

195
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:34,640
A wandering monk in the forest.

196
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:37,960
He once stayed at Khao Phrom too.

197
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:46,000
Do you know

198
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:49,360
Khun Yod's son isn't dead.

199
00:17:51,760 --> 00:17:53,160
What did you say, Yiwha?

200
00:17:53,800 --> 00:17:55,000
Yiam,

201
00:17:55,520 --> 00:17:57,800
Khun Yod's son, is still alive.

202
00:17:57,880 --> 00:17:59,480
He escaped that night.

203
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:02,960
How do you know?

204
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:05,640
I met him.

205
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:08,720
Then where is he now?

206
00:18:11,360 --> 00:18:13,400
Is something wrong, Lasor?

207
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:24,200
The governor requests your presence.

208
00:18:29,440 --> 00:18:30,720
I have to go to work.

209
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:54,600
- Uncle Niem.
- Hm?

210
00:18:54,680 --> 00:18:56,880
Do you know where Khun Yod's house is?

211
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:59,600
Khuan Phra-ngam. Why?

212
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:01,040
I want to go there.

213
00:19:01,720 --> 00:19:03,640
Why would you go? Let's just head back.

214
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:07,720
Khun Yod's son isn't dead.

215
00:19:08,720 --> 00:19:09,640
Really?

216
00:19:10,840 --> 00:19:11,760
Yes.

217
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:14,320
He'll definitely return to the house.

218
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:17,120
Uncle Niem,
can you tell me where to find him?

219
00:19:18,080 --> 00:19:19,520
I want to meet him.

220
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:36,000
Dad.

221
00:20:03,800 --> 00:20:04,960
How have you been?

222
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:29,640
Anyway,

223
00:20:30,240 --> 00:20:32,360
what are you doing here, Yiwha?

224
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:37,720
I want to know the truth
about Khun Yod's death.

225
00:20:38,760 --> 00:20:42,640
Khun Yod and I
were brothers from Khao Phrom.

226
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:45,080
We lived together, faced death together.

227
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:49,440
We even promised to bind you and Yiam
in marriage.

228
00:20:57,280 --> 00:20:59,280
If I had arrived in time that day,

229
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:03,120
Yod, his wife, and his daughter

230
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:07,040
would never have ended up

231
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:09,720
in such a horrific situation like that.

232
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:21,920
Lasor told me Bandit Pud was responsible.

233
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:26,880
But I feel like he's hiding something.

234
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:31,880
The crude sorcery
of a petty bandit like Pud

235
00:21:32,400 --> 00:21:35,080
could never bring down
a master sorcerer like Khun Yod.

236
00:21:37,320 --> 00:21:39,480
There must be more behind this.

237
00:21:40,200 --> 00:21:42,240
That's why Yod died so horribly.

238
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:51,960
Dad,

239
00:21:54,800 --> 00:21:57,440
when I went to look for Lasor
at Khao Phrom,

240
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:01,160
I met Khun Yod's son.

241
00:22:02,800 --> 00:22:03,680
Yiam?

242
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:08,840
Yiam is still alive? Where is he now?

243
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:12,800
I don't know.

244
00:22:12,880 --> 00:22:14,240
I only know that

245
00:22:14,320 --> 00:22:17,320
Yiam will definitely come back
to take revenge on you and Lasor.

246
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,120
How do you know that?

247
00:22:25,880 --> 00:22:27,520
Yiam believes

248
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:32,080
you and Lasor

249
00:22:34,560 --> 00:22:36,560
killed his family.

250
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:49,880
There's one more thing
I need the truth about.

251
00:22:52,320 --> 00:22:54,120
Nui is dead.

252
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:56,960
Huh? Nui?

253
00:22:59,280 --> 00:23:00,680
How did he die?

254
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:06,520
Lasor only said
Nui died of jungle fever last year.

255
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:11,000
But something felt wrong.

256
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:14,920
He showed no emotion at all
when he spoke of Nui's death.

257
00:23:21,520 --> 00:23:24,280
One year after being driven out
of Chum Suea,

258
00:23:25,440 --> 00:23:27,360
what exactly did Lasor go through?

259
00:23:30,840 --> 00:23:33,440
Why is he tangled up
in Yod's family's death?

260
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:35,040
And now Nui's as well?

261
00:23:45,480 --> 00:23:46,560
No.

262
00:23:47,080 --> 00:23:49,240
This is my turf. This is my home.

263
00:23:49,320 --> 00:23:51,680
You can't bring your son here

264
00:23:51,760 --> 00:23:54,200
to make a living on my land.

265
00:23:54,280 --> 00:23:58,120
Huai Yao doesn't belong to you alone.

266
00:23:58,200 --> 00:24:00,080
Can't you spare some space

267
00:24:00,160 --> 00:24:02,000
for the younger generation
to make a living?

268
00:24:02,080 --> 00:24:05,040
Don't think I don't know.

269
00:24:05,560 --> 00:24:07,680
Your son, Talong,

270
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:12,880
plans to open a trading company
to compete with me.

271
00:24:13,840 --> 00:24:15,720
What kind of father are you?

272
00:24:15,800 --> 00:24:20,960
Why don't you teach him
whose territory this is?

273
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:23,080
Well, well.

274
00:24:23,600 --> 00:24:27,960
You already monopolize the city's taxes.

275
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,880
Isn't that enough?

276
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:33,560
Hoard it all yourself
and you'll burst and die.

277
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:34,680
Hey!

278
00:24:35,720 --> 00:24:37,320
If that's how you talk,

279
00:24:38,760 --> 00:24:40,400
then there's nothing left to discuss.

280
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:45,200
Then we're done doing business.

281
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:46,760
Huh.

282
00:24:47,280 --> 00:24:51,480
I came today only as a courtesy notice.

283
00:24:51,560 --> 00:24:52,600
No matter what,

284
00:24:53,120 --> 00:24:56,280
my son will open his business in Huai Yao.

285
00:24:56,360 --> 00:24:57,880
Come what may.

286
00:25:07,360 --> 00:25:08,480
How did it go, boss?

287
00:25:20,680 --> 00:25:22,120
If you let Tycoon Thongyoo

288
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:24,040
keep monopolizing trade like this,

289
00:25:24,120 --> 00:25:25,920
the villagers will starve sooner or later.

290
00:25:26,520 --> 00:25:27,800
Don't forget.

291
00:25:27,880 --> 00:25:29,880
He's close to the governor.

292
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:32,640
You and your son need to be careful.

293
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:35,440
I know.

294
00:25:35,520 --> 00:25:38,160
- I'll be going now, Seng.
- See you.

295
00:25:47,080 --> 00:25:49,360
- Hey!
- Hurry!

296
00:25:50,960 --> 00:25:52,080
Hey!

297
00:26:02,040 --> 00:26:03,360
You wanna die?

298
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:24,240
Hey! Stop!

299
00:26:29,440 --> 00:26:32,320
Help. Help me.

300
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:05,440
Pa!

301
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:09,800
Pa! Pa!

302
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:11,720
Who did this to you?

303
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:15,000
Who did this to you?

304
00:27:15,080 --> 00:27:17,080
Why did this happen to you?

305
00:27:17,160 --> 00:27:18,720
Who did this?

306
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:21,880
Who did this to my dad?

307
00:27:22,760 --> 00:27:24,600
Who did this to my dad?

308
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:28,280
Talong…

309
00:27:31,120 --> 00:27:32,720
Your father is at peace now.

310
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:41,400
How can he be at peace

311
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:45,880
when the one who killed him
is still walking free?

312
00:27:58,880 --> 00:28:01,080
Don't worry, Pa.

313
00:28:02,440 --> 00:28:04,240
I will avenge you myself.

314
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:06,880
I swear it.

315
00:28:24,720 --> 00:28:26,400
How is he?

316
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:31,000
As you can see.

317
00:28:32,560 --> 00:28:34,440
The doctor says
he doesn't know when he'll recover.

318
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:37,520
Do you know who did this?

319
00:28:38,240 --> 00:28:40,080
Most likely Thongyoo's men.

320
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:44,840
You're a policeman.
Why haven't you dragged them to jail?

321
00:28:46,320 --> 00:28:47,800
I won't let them go.

322
00:28:49,240 --> 00:28:53,080
We're gathering evidence to arrest them.

323
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:56,680
I'm just worried about my dad.

324
00:28:57,280 --> 00:28:58,640
Don't worry about things here.

325
00:28:58,720 --> 00:29:00,560
I'll take care of him myself.

326
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:02,280
You just do your duty.

327
00:29:05,120 --> 00:29:07,040
Thank you, Noree.

328
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:08,160
Of course.

329
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:17,080
All this and it ends in murder?

330
00:29:17,160 --> 00:29:19,320
Money makes people ruthless.

331
00:29:19,840 --> 00:29:22,320
Thongyoo has the governor backing him.

332
00:29:23,960 --> 00:29:25,880
Even though a black-masked man
appeared and struck,

333
00:29:26,880 --> 00:29:28,280
he still got away.

334
00:29:29,800 --> 00:29:31,400
Then who was that man in mask?

335
00:29:32,040 --> 00:29:33,120
I don't know.

336
00:29:34,040 --> 00:29:37,360
But Thongyoo has enemies everywhere.

337
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:40,440
It could've been betrayal
from within his own ranks.

338
00:29:41,840 --> 00:29:44,520
When will karma
finally catch up with them?

339
00:29:45,480 --> 00:29:46,360
I'll be

340
00:29:48,480 --> 00:29:50,560
the karma that catches up with them.

341
00:29:51,640 --> 00:29:52,720
Wad.

342
00:29:54,400 --> 00:29:55,400
You're hard to kill, huh?

343
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:59,520
The city's burning.
People killing each other nonstop.

344
00:30:00,200 --> 00:30:01,960
How could I die so easily?

345
00:30:02,720 --> 00:30:05,480
So? Are you two willing to join me

346
00:30:06,440 --> 00:30:08,280
and wipe out those parasites
weighing down the land?

347
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:15,640
Don't rush into it.
Think about your child.

348
00:30:16,280 --> 00:30:19,200
Lasor is on their side now.

349
00:30:20,880 --> 00:30:22,200
Someone like Duang

350
00:30:23,040 --> 00:30:25,680
would never keep an enemy
like Lasor close.

351
00:30:26,200 --> 00:30:28,040
Whatever happens will happen.

352
00:30:29,080 --> 00:30:30,760
Lasor chose his own path.

353
00:30:32,120 --> 00:30:33,520
Whether good or evil,

354
00:30:34,360 --> 00:30:36,320
he'll have to accept
the fate that comes with it.

355
00:30:37,480 --> 00:30:38,840
How is Lasor doing?

356
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:41,480
Right now,

357
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:44,840
your son isn't the Lasor I once knew.

358
00:30:47,280 --> 00:30:48,720
What do you mean?

359
00:30:50,080 --> 00:30:52,440
His eyes are aggressive,
like someone else entirely.

360
00:30:53,200 --> 00:30:55,080
His face is dull, drained of all presence,

361
00:30:55,160 --> 00:30:57,760
like someone possessed or cursed.

362
00:30:58,760 --> 00:31:01,320
Go see for yourself, Wad.

363
00:31:31,720 --> 00:31:32,800
Nui.

364
00:31:40,200 --> 00:31:41,600
Go find out for me.

365
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:44,080
Where is Yiam right now?

366
00:31:46,040 --> 00:31:47,040
Yes, brother.

367
00:31:53,360 --> 00:31:54,280
Lasor.

368
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:02,440
Lasor,

369
00:32:03,560 --> 00:32:05,320
tonight is close to the new moon.

370
00:32:05,400 --> 00:32:07,800
You must hurry
before your body can't endure it anymore.

371
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:14,960
I'm starving. I can't take it anymore.

372
00:32:16,600 --> 00:32:18,560
I have to feed myself with dark sorcery.

373
00:32:48,680 --> 00:32:49,800
Who the hell are you?

374
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:54,080
You don't need to know.

375
00:32:54,160 --> 00:32:55,880
You wanna try me?

376
00:32:55,960 --> 00:32:57,000
Fine.

377
00:32:57,520 --> 00:32:59,240
<i>Om mahabid--</i>

378
00:32:59,320 --> 00:33:02,000
<i>I will draw up</i>
<i>All holy incantations to my throat</i>

379
00:33:02,080 --> 00:33:04,560
<i>I will lift</i>
<i>All holy incantations above my chest</i>

380
00:33:04,640 --> 00:33:07,400
<i>I will raise</i>
<i>All holy incantations above my head</i>

381
00:33:07,480 --> 00:33:09,880
<i>The venerable master therefore</i>
<i>Makes me supreme above all men</i>

382
00:33:09,960 --> 00:33:12,880
<i>Ehi klai klai, piyan ma-ma</i>

383
00:33:35,520 --> 00:33:38,560
That shaman's sorcery should
keep you going for several more days,

384
00:33:39,080 --> 00:33:40,960
until the night of the new moon comes.

385
00:33:42,400 --> 00:33:44,160
I have to keep siphoning sorcery

386
00:33:44,680 --> 00:33:46,320
to heal myself.

387
00:33:47,160 --> 00:33:48,280
Otherwise,

388
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:50,720
the darkness inside me

389
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:53,120
will turn around and devour me.

390
00:33:53,640 --> 00:33:56,000
Everything is in your hands now.

391
00:33:56,600 --> 00:33:58,360
Why don't you kill Duang already?

392
00:33:58,440 --> 00:33:59,840
Have you forgotten?

393
00:33:59,920 --> 00:34:01,920
He's the one who destroyed Chum Suea.

394
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:03,400
I've never forgotten.

395
00:34:07,800 --> 00:34:09,600
But Duang is still useful to me.

396
00:34:10,639 --> 00:34:12,719
Let him appoint me as an official first.

397
00:34:14,239 --> 00:34:15,719
Then I'll kill him for sure.

398
00:34:15,800 --> 00:34:19,520
Why not use sorcery to control him,
make him do whatever you want?

399
00:34:23,040 --> 00:34:24,320
If I control him with sorcery

400
00:34:25,440 --> 00:34:27,280
and force him to appoint me,

401
00:34:27,960 --> 00:34:29,520
the authorities will grow suspicious

402
00:34:30,199 --> 00:34:32,440
and send a royal commissioner
to investigate.

403
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:33,679
Then I'm finished.

404
00:34:35,840 --> 00:34:37,920
I still need to build influence.

405
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:40,440
When the time comes,

406
00:34:41,400 --> 00:34:44,320
the governor's seat of Tha Khiri
will be mine.

407
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:58,240
Someone's following us.

408
00:35:54,720 --> 00:35:56,040
Help me.

409
00:36:18,800 --> 00:36:19,920
Master?

410
00:36:30,560 --> 00:36:33,400
Your mind is restless. In turmoil.

411
00:36:34,440 --> 00:36:36,280
Why does my body

412
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:40,680
feel like it's burning alive, Old Master?

413
00:36:42,840 --> 00:36:46,480
Klaikot Lek Lai is a sacred mineral,

414
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:49,520
born only from the immense spiritual power

415
00:36:49,600 --> 00:36:51,120
of a pure, disciplined hermit.

416
00:36:52,200 --> 00:36:55,000
If your heart is steadfast in virtue,

417
00:36:55,080 --> 00:36:59,040
it becomes armor,
shielding you so no danger may touch you.

418
00:36:59,640 --> 00:37:03,520
But when your mind is ruled
by unwholesome fire,

419
00:37:03,600 --> 00:37:07,160
greed, delusion, and anger,

420
00:37:07,760 --> 00:37:11,040
it will burn you,
tormenting you with searing pain.

421
00:37:13,800 --> 00:37:15,040
Then

422
00:37:15,560 --> 00:37:18,520
how do I control
the power of Lek Lai, Master?

423
00:37:18,600 --> 00:37:21,280
Extinguish the three fires in your heart.

424
00:37:22,320 --> 00:37:26,240
Let go. Accept. Be calm.

425
00:37:52,120 --> 00:37:54,680
<i>Extinguish the three fires in your heart.</i>

426
00:37:55,760 --> 00:37:59,840
<i>Let go. Accept. Be calm.</i>

427
00:38:02,200 --> 00:38:03,760
The three fires?

428
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:20,600
Good.

429
00:38:21,120 --> 00:38:24,800
He didn't report it.
He came to kill me himself.

430
00:38:26,640 --> 00:38:28,480
You're rushing straight
to your own death, Yiam.

431
00:38:29,160 --> 00:38:32,160
He didn't even get a chance.
He tucked his tail and ran.

432
00:38:37,040 --> 00:38:38,680
Want me to chase him down and kill him?

433
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:42,880
He's just a fledgling bird.
What could he possibly do to me?

434
00:38:43,480 --> 00:38:44,960
Don't be careless, Lasor.

435
00:38:45,040 --> 00:38:47,720
If he dared come alone,

436
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:49,840
he must be carrying something powerful.

437
00:38:51,240 --> 00:38:52,080
Good.

438
00:38:54,040 --> 00:38:55,400
Let him come.

439
00:38:56,560 --> 00:38:58,520
I'm always ready to welcome him.

440
00:39:10,480 --> 00:39:12,240
Who was Lasor talking to?

441
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:14,480
What if he was talking
to the ghost he keeps?

442
00:39:14,560 --> 00:39:17,600
Nonsense. What ghost?

443
00:39:17,680 --> 00:39:19,320
I've heard

444
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:22,560
people who practice sorcery
keep spirits to serve them,

445
00:39:22,640 --> 00:39:24,640
or whispering entities.

446
00:39:26,640 --> 00:39:29,640
Lasor? That powerful?

447
00:39:29,720 --> 00:39:31,840
I don't believe it.
Not in a million years.

448
00:39:32,800 --> 00:39:33,880
Don't believe what,

449
00:39:34,480 --> 00:39:35,840
My Lady?

450
00:39:38,200 --> 00:39:40,600
I'm talking to my sister. Don't butt in.

451
00:39:42,880 --> 00:39:44,800
If you don't believe me,

452
00:39:45,440 --> 00:39:47,040
shall I summon a ghost for you to see?

453
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:51,920
Go on then. If you're really that good,
summon one right now.

454
00:39:52,520 --> 00:39:54,720
Don't summon it. I'm scared.

455
00:39:57,400 --> 00:39:58,600
And you, Lady Duen?

456
00:39:59,200 --> 00:40:00,720
Aren't you afraid of ghosts?

457
00:40:02,160 --> 00:40:03,560
I'm not afraid.

458
00:40:05,040 --> 00:40:06,760
Look at you now.

459
00:40:06,840 --> 00:40:08,560
You're scarier than any ghost.

460
00:40:13,600 --> 00:40:14,680
Good.

461
00:40:17,200 --> 00:40:19,760
I like a woman with guts.

462
00:40:21,440 --> 00:40:23,040
If you don't mind,

463
00:40:23,960 --> 00:40:26,000
I'll take you to see a ghost together.

464
00:40:49,800 --> 00:40:51,000
We're in trouble, sir.

465
00:40:52,440 --> 00:40:53,680
What is it?

466
00:40:54,280 --> 00:40:55,520
Who is this?

467
00:40:55,600 --> 00:40:58,240
Who allowed you cops into my house?

468
00:40:58,320 --> 00:40:59,360
Huh?

469
00:40:59,880 --> 00:41:02,240
Tycoon Thongyoo. Mr. Song.

470
00:41:02,320 --> 00:41:03,480
Please come give a statement
at the station.

471
00:41:05,680 --> 00:41:09,080
You probably don't know
who you're messing with.

472
00:41:09,680 --> 00:41:13,000
Get out, unless you want trouble.

473
00:41:13,600 --> 00:41:15,440
There are laws in this country.

474
00:41:15,960 --> 00:41:17,640
Anyone who breaks them

475
00:41:18,440 --> 00:41:20,240
must be punished under the law.

476
00:41:20,960 --> 00:41:23,080
Take them to the station.

477
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:29,880
Hey! Let go! Let go! What did I do?

478
00:41:29,960 --> 00:41:31,760
Let go of me.

479
00:41:34,680 --> 00:41:35,600
PATROL UNIT

480
00:41:35,680 --> 00:41:39,760
My father testified
that you hired Mr. Song and his men

481
00:41:40,400 --> 00:41:42,320
to kill Jin Yuan and my father.

482
00:41:43,080 --> 00:41:46,880
I don't know anything.

483
00:41:49,160 --> 00:41:50,680
I know nothing about this.

484
00:41:50,760 --> 00:41:52,680
A witness saw you

485
00:41:52,760 --> 00:41:55,560
shoot Jin Yuan and my father
in front of the teahouse,

486
00:41:55,640 --> 00:41:57,160
and you still dare to deny it?

487
00:41:58,720 --> 00:42:00,600
I told you.

488
00:42:01,120 --> 00:42:02,760
I don't know anything.

489
00:42:04,720 --> 00:42:07,080
Lock them up. Hold them pending trial.

490
00:42:07,160 --> 00:42:09,560
- Hey! You can't do this to me!
- Hey!

491
00:42:09,640 --> 00:42:12,160
I'm close to the governor.

492
00:42:12,240 --> 00:42:14,800
You can't disgrace me like this.

493
00:42:14,880 --> 00:42:16,240
Take them away.

494
00:42:16,320 --> 00:42:18,600
- Go!
- Let go!

495
00:42:18,680 --> 00:42:19,960
Easy now. We can talk.

496
00:42:20,040 --> 00:42:20,960
WANTED

497
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:23,440
We're all friends here.

498
00:42:25,600 --> 00:42:26,680
Sir Lasor,

499
00:42:28,480 --> 00:42:30,120
what are you doing here?

500
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:33,920
If you're here to use your power

501
00:42:34,800 --> 00:42:37,200
to get the tycoon released,

502
00:42:38,200 --> 00:42:40,080
then please leave,.

503
00:42:42,320 --> 00:42:43,600
Why would I help him?

504
00:42:44,720 --> 00:42:47,560
He framed my father

505
00:42:47,640 --> 00:42:49,400
as the bandit who robbed him.

506
00:42:52,400 --> 00:42:55,480
Let him taste prison bars for once.

507
00:42:56,160 --> 00:42:59,480
Sir Lasor, why joke like this?

508
00:42:59,560 --> 00:43:01,480
You're making me uneasy.

509
00:43:01,560 --> 00:43:03,360
I don't joke.

510
00:43:05,880 --> 00:43:09,040
So tell me,

511
00:43:09,640 --> 00:43:11,440
who robbed your house?

512
00:43:15,640 --> 00:43:18,680
Bandit Yai. He robbed my house,

513
00:43:18,760 --> 00:43:20,480
not Bandit Wad.

514
00:43:20,560 --> 00:43:22,640
My eyes and ears
aren't what they used to be.

515
00:43:23,160 --> 00:43:24,920
I must've mixed it up.

516
00:43:25,880 --> 00:43:28,840
- You're sure?
- Yes.

517
00:43:33,440 --> 00:43:34,880
Did you hear that clearly?

518
00:43:35,800 --> 00:43:37,320
Not my father.

519
00:43:41,800 --> 00:43:44,000
Even if he retracts the old testimony,

520
00:43:46,120 --> 00:43:48,320
the new charge, murder,

521
00:43:49,240 --> 00:43:50,680
still stands.

522
00:43:55,640 --> 00:43:58,720
This matter is delicate.

523
00:43:58,800 --> 00:44:01,640
It involves
the Chinese merchants' association

524
00:44:01,720 --> 00:44:03,640
doing business in Tha Khiri.

525
00:44:04,800 --> 00:44:07,320
So the governor has instructed me
to inform you that

526
00:44:10,240 --> 00:44:11,760
His Excellency

527
00:44:12,280 --> 00:44:14,720
will personally investigate this case.

528
00:44:16,080 --> 00:44:17,320
I trust the police

529
00:44:17,840 --> 00:44:19,040
have no objections.

530
00:44:24,760 --> 00:44:27,120
If you're going to act,
learn to respect my name first.

531
00:44:27,200 --> 00:44:29,160
All you do is bring me headaches.

532
00:44:29,880 --> 00:44:31,760
If it were not
for His Excellency's protection,

533
00:44:31,840 --> 00:44:34,240
you'd already be
swatting mosquitoes in a cell.

534
00:44:34,880 --> 00:44:38,240
I admit it. This time I was wrong.

535
00:44:38,320 --> 00:44:40,560
From now on, I'll be careful.

536
00:44:40,640 --> 00:44:43,280
I won't let this happen again.

537
00:44:44,200 --> 00:44:46,160
If you were going to kill them,

538
00:44:46,240 --> 00:44:48,200
you should've silenced them all.

539
00:44:48,800 --> 00:44:50,720
But you let Jin Seng live.

540
00:44:51,440 --> 00:44:53,640
If that masked man hadn't interfered,

541
00:44:53,720 --> 00:44:55,720
I would've killed him already, sir.

542
00:44:55,800 --> 00:44:58,880
Did you see his face?

543
00:44:58,960 --> 00:45:00,400
No, sir.

544
00:45:00,480 --> 00:45:02,440
He covered his face and eyes
with black cloth.

545
00:45:05,760 --> 00:45:06,760
Tim,

546
00:45:07,680 --> 00:45:09,680
send our men to investigate.

547
00:45:09,760 --> 00:45:12,640
Find out who that masked man is.

548
00:45:13,600 --> 00:45:15,960
How dare he declare himself my enemy?

549
00:45:16,040 --> 00:45:17,080
Yes, Your Excellency.

550
00:45:17,160 --> 00:45:19,080
As for Jin Seng,

551
00:45:19,160 --> 00:45:21,200
I'll send Lasor to kill him.

552
00:45:25,720 --> 00:45:27,800
I'll borrow his hand to do the dirty work.

553
00:45:28,600 --> 00:45:31,600
Lasor will become
the evil sorcerer bandit.

554
00:45:32,120 --> 00:45:34,400
Then I'll report to the capital,

555
00:45:34,480 --> 00:45:38,120
requesting they send
a powerful practitioner to eliminate him.

556
00:45:38,200 --> 00:45:39,840
That way,

557
00:45:39,920 --> 00:45:42,520
two birds with one stone.

558
00:45:45,160 --> 00:45:48,280
And what if the people
the authorities send

559
00:45:48,360 --> 00:45:50,040
to handle Lasor

560
00:45:50,120 --> 00:45:54,320
turn against us instead?

561
00:45:54,840 --> 00:45:57,120
Wouldn't that create a bigger problem?

562
00:45:59,280 --> 00:46:03,560
Even iron bends when money is applied.

563
00:46:04,400 --> 00:46:06,880
Everything can be fixed with money.

564
00:46:07,560 --> 00:46:08,840
Right?

565
00:46:25,360 --> 00:46:26,920
I arrest them, they get released.

566
00:46:28,840 --> 00:46:31,640
The law here is so damn sacred, huh?

567
00:46:32,640 --> 00:46:35,040
You're drunk, Pun.

568
00:46:36,080 --> 00:46:37,800
You can't go back on duty.

569
00:46:37,880 --> 00:46:39,280
Screw it.

570
00:46:40,000 --> 00:46:41,720
This place is lawless.

571
00:46:42,240 --> 00:46:43,920
Whoever wants to rob, robs.

572
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:46,160
- Whoever wants to kill, kills.
- Pun.

573
00:46:46,840 --> 00:46:48,120
Keep your voice down.

574
00:46:48,760 --> 00:46:50,400
If someone hears you,
we're all in trouble.

575
00:46:54,360 --> 00:46:55,640
Chang.

576
00:46:56,440 --> 00:46:57,880
Go get me more liquor.

577
00:46:59,040 --> 00:47:01,320
Hurry up, mine's finished.

578
00:47:09,920 --> 00:47:12,280
- Hurry, Chang.
- Fine.

579
00:47:27,840 --> 00:47:29,880
Enough. Stop drinking.

580
00:47:31,240 --> 00:47:33,760
What is it with you and your brother?

581
00:47:34,800 --> 00:47:36,480
Why do you keep getting in my way?

582
00:47:38,240 --> 00:47:40,560
Oh, I just realized.

583
00:47:42,680 --> 00:47:45,920
You two are Bandit Wad's kids.

584
00:47:47,280 --> 00:47:48,960
Bandits side with bandits.

585
00:47:49,560 --> 00:47:51,480
I know you're angry at Lasor.

586
00:47:52,000 --> 00:47:53,520
But what does that have to do
with me and Dad?

587
00:47:56,120 --> 00:47:57,160
In no time at all,

588
00:47:58,040 --> 00:48:00,760
your brother cleared himself
and your father of every accusation.

589
00:48:01,880 --> 00:48:03,640
Black turned white.

590
00:48:04,360 --> 00:48:05,600
Wrong turned right.

591
00:48:07,480 --> 00:48:10,000
I'm so proud of your father
and your brother.

592
00:48:11,240 --> 00:48:13,360
Doing whatever it takes for themselves,

593
00:48:14,000 --> 00:48:17,280
even if it means throwing away
their humanity.

594
00:48:17,960 --> 00:48:19,520
That's too much, Pun.

595
00:48:20,320 --> 00:48:22,000
Don't you dare insult my father.

596
00:48:23,080 --> 00:48:24,280
Right!

597
00:48:25,360 --> 00:48:26,840
Your father's a saint.

598
00:48:27,440 --> 00:48:29,680
No one more noble than him.

599
00:48:30,280 --> 00:48:31,480
- Pun!
- Hey.

600
00:48:32,480 --> 00:48:34,320
Stop it, Pun.

601
00:48:35,400 --> 00:48:37,200
Stop what?

602
00:48:37,280 --> 00:48:39,120
That's still nothing

603
00:48:39,680 --> 00:48:41,640
compared to the vile shit
they did to my dad.

604
00:48:42,760 --> 00:48:45,800
You love your father. I love mine.

605
00:48:45,880 --> 00:48:48,480
Quit barking like a rabid dog
before I lose my patience.

606
00:48:48,560 --> 00:48:50,240
Yiwha, let's go.

607
00:48:52,240 --> 00:48:53,280
Come on.

608
00:49:01,800 --> 00:49:03,400
Calm down.

609
00:49:03,920 --> 00:49:05,280
You shouldn't have stopped me.

610
00:49:05,360 --> 00:49:08,440
I wanted to punch his teeth in.

611
00:49:08,520 --> 00:49:11,480
Pun is drunk. Don't take it to heart.

612
00:49:11,560 --> 00:49:13,160
If he insults me, I can take it.

613
00:49:13,240 --> 00:49:15,200
But insulting my father, I can't.

614
00:49:16,280 --> 00:49:17,880
Lasor…

615
00:49:17,960 --> 00:49:19,640
He never should've
gotten involved in this.

616
00:49:19,720 --> 00:49:21,760
Now my dad and I
are cursed right along with him.

617
00:49:21,840 --> 00:49:25,200
Maybe your brother
was forced by the governor.

618
00:49:25,800 --> 00:49:28,520
Lasor isn't someone even Dad can control.

619
00:49:29,040 --> 00:49:31,000
He must have his reasons.

620
00:49:32,360 --> 00:49:33,520
What reason?

621
00:49:39,680 --> 00:49:41,160
It's just arresting one man.

622
00:49:41,720 --> 00:49:43,160
Why does it have to be me?

623
00:49:43,240 --> 00:49:45,840
Jin Seng is secretly building power,

624
00:49:45,920 --> 00:49:48,760
setting himself up as a triad boss,
smuggling opium.

625
00:49:48,840 --> 00:49:50,720
But I can't touch him,

626
00:49:51,240 --> 00:49:54,560
because his son, Pun,
is in the police force.

627
00:49:56,720 --> 00:49:58,040
Pun…

628
00:49:58,920 --> 00:50:00,760
Your father isn't any better than mine.

629
00:50:12,960 --> 00:50:16,800
If you help me eliminate Jin Seng,
the triad leader,

630
00:50:18,040 --> 00:50:20,040
I'll recommend you for a reward.

631
00:50:20,680 --> 00:50:23,120
I'll appoint you deputy governor.

632
00:50:25,320 --> 00:50:26,800
You'll have rank and status.

633
00:50:27,400 --> 00:50:30,920
Something fitting for the future
son-in-law of Tha Khiri's governor.

634
00:50:37,200 --> 00:50:39,320
Are you sure, Tim?

635
00:50:39,400 --> 00:50:40,320
Yes, sir.

636
00:50:40,400 --> 00:50:43,040
Lasor is clearly in love with Lady Duen.

637
00:50:44,160 --> 00:50:47,280
I'm afraid he'll use sorcery
and destroy my daughter.

638
00:50:47,360 --> 00:50:48,960
He won't dare, sir.

639
00:50:49,600 --> 00:50:52,120
He truly loves Miss Duen.

640
00:50:52,200 --> 00:50:53,880
You can rest assured.

641
00:50:53,960 --> 00:50:55,800
Then what do you want me to do?

642
00:50:56,320 --> 00:50:58,800
Offer Duen up to him on a platter?

643
00:50:58,880 --> 00:51:00,160
Never.

644
00:51:00,240 --> 00:51:01,520
No matter

645
00:51:02,040 --> 00:51:04,080
how powerful a man is,

646
00:51:04,160 --> 00:51:06,280
he still falls to a woman.

647
00:51:09,640 --> 00:51:11,360
What do you mean, sir?

648
00:51:18,560 --> 00:51:19,760
I know

649
00:51:20,280 --> 00:51:23,000
you like my daughter, Duen.

650
00:51:25,600 --> 00:51:27,880
If you build merit,

651
00:51:27,960 --> 00:51:30,320
rise in rank, become a <i>khun</i>, a <i>muen</i>,

652
00:51:30,920 --> 00:51:32,640
then I'll feel at ease.

653
00:51:33,280 --> 00:51:35,400
And I'll entrust my daughter to you.

654
00:51:36,720 --> 00:51:37,800
Interested?

655
00:51:50,160 --> 00:51:52,560
Why do you have to use me as bait?

656
00:51:54,120 --> 00:51:56,040
Lasor is dangerous in every way.

657
00:51:57,920 --> 00:52:00,000
But his weakness is you.

658
00:52:01,600 --> 00:52:04,400
So I'll use you
to make him lower his guard.

659
00:52:04,480 --> 00:52:06,200
Then we find a way to get rid of him.

660
00:52:18,600 --> 00:52:20,360
And if you fail?

661
00:52:20,440 --> 00:52:23,000
Do I become Lasor's wife?

662
00:52:23,600 --> 00:52:25,920
As long as I'm breathing,

663
00:52:26,560 --> 00:52:29,400
I won't let him touch you.

664
00:52:30,000 --> 00:52:31,080
Believe me.

665
00:52:44,520 --> 00:52:46,400
<i>‪-Dad!</i>
<i>‪-Dad!</i>

666
00:52:46,480 --> 00:52:48,680
<i>‪-Dad!</i>
<i>‪-Dad!</i>

667
00:52:49,960 --> 00:52:50,800
<i>‪Dad!</i>

668
00:52:56,080 --> 00:52:57,320
<i>‪Dad!</i>

669
00:52:58,400 --> 00:53:01,200
You hellish beast! I'll kill you!

670
00:53:15,280 --> 00:53:17,240
You haven't eaten for days, Talong.

671
00:53:18,000 --> 00:53:19,720
If you don't eat,

672
00:53:19,800 --> 00:53:22,040
where will you find the strength
to fight them?

673
00:53:23,320 --> 00:53:24,520
I don't know.

674
00:53:25,120 --> 00:53:26,280
You can't say that.

675
00:53:26,800 --> 00:53:28,760
Your enemy isn't ordinary.

676
00:53:30,520 --> 00:53:32,120
If you think only of revenge,

677
00:53:32,200 --> 00:53:34,480
you're no different
from a moth flying into a flame.

678
00:53:35,920 --> 00:53:37,800
No matter how powerful they are,

679
00:53:40,400 --> 00:53:42,720
I swear before my father's spirit

680
00:53:43,640 --> 00:53:45,440
I'll bring them down.

681
00:53:46,480 --> 00:53:49,480
Even if it costs me my life.

682
00:54:14,280 --> 00:54:15,360
Pun.

683
00:54:23,240 --> 00:54:24,720
How's my dad?

684
00:54:26,080 --> 00:54:28,720
He ate, took his medicine,
and just fell asleep.

685
00:54:33,680 --> 00:54:35,520
You work at Uncle Chaem's place,

686
00:54:36,800 --> 00:54:38,800
and still come help take care of him.

687
00:54:39,840 --> 00:54:41,520
You must be exhausted, Noree.

688
00:54:44,520 --> 00:54:46,360
I'm not tired.

689
00:54:47,120 --> 00:54:50,440
If there's anything I can do, I'll do it.

690
00:54:58,200 --> 00:55:01,040
Noree, I…

691
00:55:08,280 --> 00:55:09,960
I'll go on patrol now, alright?

692
00:55:12,800 --> 00:55:13,880
Alright.

693
00:55:31,200 --> 00:55:33,160
I have to find you

694
00:55:34,600 --> 00:55:36,560
before it's too late.

695
00:55:43,160 --> 00:55:44,120
Blur.

696
00:55:49,440 --> 00:55:51,160
There is no Blur anymore.

697
00:55:54,520 --> 00:55:55,960
Only Yiam,

698
00:55:56,880 --> 00:55:59,880
Khun Yod's son, whose entire family
was slaughtered by Bandit Wad and his son.

699
00:56:01,160 --> 00:56:02,680
Listen to me.

700
00:56:03,280 --> 00:56:06,320
My father and brother didn't do it.

701
00:56:07,560 --> 00:56:09,920
Of course you'd side with them.

702
00:56:10,720 --> 00:56:12,760
Blood is always thicker than water.

703
00:56:35,640 --> 00:56:37,360
From now on,

704
00:56:39,840 --> 00:56:42,560
let's pretend we never knew each other.

705
00:56:58,760 --> 00:57:00,600
I already belong to you.

706
00:57:02,160 --> 00:57:03,720
You're really going to

707
00:57:05,400 --> 00:57:06,600
abandon me?

708
00:57:14,240 --> 00:57:17,480
Klaikot Lek Lai
is forged by a righteous hermit.

709
00:57:17,560 --> 00:57:19,520
Don't you evil men dare possess it.

710
00:57:19,600 --> 00:57:22,360
<i>Rip the Lek Lai out of his body.</i>
<i>Then you can kill him.</i>

711
00:57:22,440 --> 00:57:23,640
They're the governor's men.

712
00:57:23,720 --> 00:57:26,560
Even if we catch them,
Duang will just release them.

713
00:57:26,640 --> 00:57:28,520
I'll write to my superiors

714
00:57:29,120 --> 00:57:31,760
<i>and have them send down</i>
<i>a powerful sorcerer.</i>

715
00:57:31,840 --> 00:57:33,640
<i>One who can deal with Lasor.</i>

716
00:57:33,720 --> 00:57:37,160
<i>Ehi-klai klai-piyang-ma.</i>

717
00:57:38,800 --> 00:57:40,640
<i>But what you choose to do next</i>

718
00:57:40,720 --> 00:57:42,760
depends entirely on your child.

719
00:57:43,360 --> 00:57:45,960
I'll drag you two back

720
00:57:46,040 --> 00:57:47,440
to face the karma you created.

721
00:57:48,600 --> 00:57:49,920
All this time,

722
00:57:50,480 --> 00:57:52,120
did you ever love me at all?

723
00:58:38,200 --> 00:58:41,800
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
